OL,3,CWhere will your tip go? New law stops
OL,4,Cbusinesses pocketing staff tips
OL,6,F"It's another example of costs being
OL,7,Fplaced on a sector that can least
OL,8,Fafford it, and we continue to urge the
OL,9,FChancellor to bring down hospitality's
OL,10,Fcost burden at the Budget, primarily
OL,11,Fthrough taking action to avoid the
OL,12,Fbillion-pound business rates bombshell
OL,13,Fset to hit the sector next year when
OL,14,Frelief ends."
OL,16,FJustin Madders, minister for
OL,17,Femployment rights, said: "This is just
OL,18,Fthe first step of many in protecting
OL,19,Fworkers and placing them at the heart
OL,20,Fof our economy.
